    <item>
      <title>The Way of the Owl - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2024/10/17/way-of-the-owl/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2024/10/17/way-of-the-owl/</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 17 Oct 2024 23:42:23 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-7732" class="post-7732 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;The Way of the Owl&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Octavian was still sick yesterday, so I gave him some more medicine. But by today, he was feeling better. He thanked me by giving me a parquet floor.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/octavian-thanks-150x112.jpg" alt="Octavian: Thanks for watchin' my back when I was down." class="wp-image-7736" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Last week, I mentioned that Whitney&amp;#8217;s house looks really nice. I&amp;#8217;m not the only one who thinks so, because she told me that the Happy Room Academy gave her 5,071 points. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/whitney-5k-150x112.jpg" alt="Whitney: The result? 5,071 points! Not bad, huh? In fact, it's pretty great!" class="wp-image-7733" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;That might not sound high compared to player houses (which are bigger and have multiple rooms), but that&amp;#8217;s really high for a villager! Usually when they say their house score, it&amp;#8217;s a 3-digit score.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;When I visited Drift today, he asked if I thought his house was nice. The two options were &amp;#8220;Yeah!&amp;#8221; and &amp;#8220;I&amp;#8217;ve seen better.&amp;#8221; Since I saw the same dialogue recently and answered &amp;#8220;yeah,&amp;#8221; I decided to pick the other option today, just to see how he reacted. And he didn&amp;#8217;t disappoint. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/drift-wreck-150x112.jpg" alt="Drift: Whoa, champ! Better check yourself before I wreck you, rrrrribbit!" class="wp-image-7734" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Don&amp;#8217;t wreck me, frog boy. I&amp;#8217;m just messing with you. 😆&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I found a note in a bottle on the beach, and it was a bit of a downer.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/note-farewell2024-150x112.jpg" alt="Listen up! If you're reading this, it's probably too late for me! Take care of things for me, would you? Farewell." class="wp-image-7740" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Saharah was in town, and she asked me to make some deliveries for her. The first one was a carpet for Blathers, who I had to wake up. Being sleepy in daytime is &amp;#8220;the way of the owl,&amp;#8221; he said. 🦉&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/blathers-wayofowl-150x112.jpg" alt="Blathers: I can't help but be sleepy during the day, I'm afraid. 'Tis the way of the owl!" class="wp-image-7735" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Next, I took a carpet for Phyllis over to town hall (and gave it to Pelly). Saharah then rewarded me with a shoji screen.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/saharah-shojilunar-150x112.jpg" alt="Saharah: Do you want a shoji screen or a lunar surface?" class="wp-image-7737" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;When I visited Caroline, she told me she would like some pink furniture. As I was walking out her door, I realized that I actually &lt;em&gt;had &lt;/em&gt;a piece of pink lovely furniture in my pockets already! So I went right back in and gave her the lovely dresser.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/caroline-how-150x112.jpg" alt="Caroline: How in the world did you know I was into collecting pink furniture?" class="wp-image-7738" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;You literally just asked me for it.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She rewarded me with a round carpet. I left and re-entered her house again, just to see if she put the dresser on display; she did.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/clean-up-150x112.jpg" alt="Me, looking into Caroline's dresser: Wow! Is it THAT hard to clean up a little before having guests over?" class="wp-image-7739" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;How could it be that messy already???&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Have a great day (or night), and I&amp;#8217;ll see you next time! Never Stop Crossing!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c27d879b16e3317f0d6fa350680e5023?s=98&amp;#038;d=mm&amp;#038;r=g' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt; &lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2024/10/17/way-of-the-owl/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2024-10-17T19:42:23-04:00"&gt;October 17, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2024-10-17T19:42:24-04:00"&gt;October 17, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/octavian-thanks.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Midge and Chip? - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACCF Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2024/10/12/midge-and-chip/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2024/10/12/midge-and-chip/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 13 Oct 2024 03:55:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-13040" class="post-13040 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Midge and Chip?&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;I missed today&amp;#8217;s fishing tournament (though I did participate in &lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/10/12/100-million-bells/"&gt;New Horizons&lt;/a&gt;), but Chip informed me of the results: Midge was the big winner with her 46-inch sea bass. Congrats, Midge!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Antonio asked me to make a delivery for him, and I was happy to help. I trotted the gift over to Roscoe; it was a Dutch shirt.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="500" height="280" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/accf-roscoe-fit-sm-150x84.jpg" alt="Roscoe: Well, let's see how she fits, giddyup!" class="wp-image-13041" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Roscoe was happy with it, and he looked very pretty in his new dress! 😆 &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/RUU_8036-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Roscoe wearing his new dress." class="wp-image-13042" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;When I returned to Antonio, he rewarded me with a new hearth.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Midge was talking about how she was so impressed by Chip&amp;#8217;s appetite, especially the way he gobbles down every fish you give him without hesitation. She even started imagining being &lt;em&gt;married &lt;/em&gt;to him!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/RUU_8037-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Midge: Could you imagine being married to Chip? You'd spend all your time in the kitchen, frying up fish!" class="wp-image-13043" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But then she clarified that &lt;em&gt;she &lt;/em&gt;didn&amp;#8217;t want to marry him. It was a weird bit of dialogue, though.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="280" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/accf-midge-chip-sm-150x84.jpg" alt="Midge: ...Oh, no, wait, I'm not saying I want to marry Chip or anything like that, I eat bugs!" class="wp-image-13044" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I sold a little fruit while I waited for 8:00 for K.K. Slider to appear, and then I headed to the Roost. I asked the traveling musician for a random song, and he performed Agent K.K. for me.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/RUU_8038-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="K.K.: All right, get ready to dig the riffs on this ditty: Agent K.K.." class="wp-image-13045" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Shortly after that, I wrapped up my game for the night. Did any of you attend K.K.&amp;#8217;s show tonight, or am I the only one who still does? 😆 Leave a comment below, and I&amp;#8217;ll see you all next time.&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2024/10/12/midge-and-chip/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2024-10-12T23:55:00-04:00"&gt;October 12, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2024-10-13T00:59:43-04:00"&gt;October 13, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/accf-roscoe-fit-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>100 Million Bells - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/10/12/100-million-bells/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/10/12/100-million-bells/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 12 Oct 2024 23:09:31 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8384" class="post-8384 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;100 Million Bells&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Sunday (the day after being &amp;#8220;purified&amp;#8221;), Katrina sent me a lucky gold turtle figurine. So I &lt;em&gt;did &lt;/em&gt;get an item from her after all! This is what it looks like:&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/gold-turtle-figurine-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="The gold turtle figurine from Katrina." class="wp-image-8387" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;On Wednesday, Anicotti the ugly Muppet mouse was camping at my campsite. I had zero interest in letting her move in. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/anicotti-camper-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Anicotti, at the campsite: Hi there! I'm Anicotti! I'm here on a camping trip! You live on this island? Tres cool." class="wp-image-8388" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;There was a heavy meteor shower last night, and I wished on a bunch of shooting stars.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/wish2024-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Wishing on a shooting star." class="wp-image-8389" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;As a result, I found 17 star fragments and three Libra fragments on the beach today.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The fall fishing tournament was underway this afternoon, so I gave it a go. On my first attempt, I caught six fish in the three-minute limit, which was good for eight points.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/tourney-6-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Reel it in! The Fishing Tourney is over!" class="wp-image-8390" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;C.J. paid me 2,250 bells for those six fish, and I decided to play again. But my second attempt was even worse: I only caught four fish, although I caught a 5th one at the buzzer that didn&amp;#8217;t count. He paid me 5,580 for those fish. I then redeemed ten points for a reward, a fish doorplate.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Since he was in town though, I decided to get a bunch of fish out of storage for him. It included the last of my summer shark hauls. I sold the 32 fish to C.J. for 524,400 bells.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="620" height="247" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/32fish-sm-250x100.jpg" alt="The 32 fish I sold to C.J." class="wp-image-8386" sizes="(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;That was a nice chunk of change, and I immediately went into town hall to deposit my money. Thanks to this influx of fishy bells, I was able to bump my savings balance up to 100 million bells for the first time!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/100m-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Savings Balance: 100,000,000 bells." class="wp-image-8391" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;This is the 2nd Animal Crossing game in which I&amp;#8217;ve reached this milestone, with New Leaf being the other. Of course, bells were considerably harder to earn in the older games.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;There isn&amp;#8217;t a K.K. Slider concert tonight due to the tournament. But here are a few other quick notes about this past week:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;I helped Gulliver on Tuesday, and he sent me another sombrero.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Flick was in town on Wednesday, and he paid me 97k for 19 bugs.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;I returned a lost item to Bob yesterday, and he rewarded me with a delivery jacket.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;I shot down a balloon present and found 30,000 bells inside. 💰&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Today, I caught three banded dragonflies! I actually saw one other one too, but it got away.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/10/12/100-million-bells/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2024-10-12T19:09:31-04:00"&gt;October 12, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2024-10-12T19:15:44-04:00"&gt;October 12, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/gold-turtle-figurine-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Acorn Festival 2024 - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2024/10/10/acorn-festival-2024/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2024/10/10/acorn-festival-2024/</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 10 Oct 2024 23:02:09 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-7718" class="post-7718 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Acorn Festival 2024&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;The Acorn Festival is underway, and Cornimer was standing outside of town hall for the event. He started things off by giving me my fortune.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/acorn-fortune2024-150x112.jpg" alt="Your secret fortune: Mini Acorn. Life: 50-50 chance. Hopes: Make a decision. Karma: Do ten chin-ups. Look behind you!" class="wp-image-7719" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I have a 50-50 chance at life? I&amp;#8217;m not sure what that means, but I seem to be alive at the moment, so I guess I&amp;#8217;m doing okay? 😆&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I gave him my first six acorns, and he gave me a mush stool.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/cornimer-watching-150x112.jpg" alt="Cornimer: And remember, li'l oakie... The great and mighty Cornimer is always watching!" class="wp-image-7720" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I went around town, picking up acorns as I went. Filbert told me that it was raining acorns! That&amp;#8217;s not exactly true, but I knew what he meant. Kinda. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/filbert-acorns-150x112.jpg" alt="Filbert: It's raining acorns! They're just falling from the sky!" class="wp-image-7721" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Many of my villagers were talking about Cornimer, and in some cases, they were even singing songs about him.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/bones-cornimer-150x112.jpg" alt="Bones: Take off your hat! And look around! 'Cause Cornimer has come to town!" class="wp-image-7722" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;And Truffles? Well, she was being her usual rude self.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/truffles-jealous-150x112.jpg" alt="Truffles: I'm doing SOOOOO good!! ...WHAT?! You don't CARE how I'm doing?! JEALOUS MUCH?!" class="wp-image-7723" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;At &lt;s&gt;GameStop&lt;/s&gt; Nookington&amp;#8217;s, I traded in some &lt;s&gt;used video games&lt;/s&gt; rotten acorns for some big money. 😉 &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/nook-8bells-150x112.jpg" alt="Tom Nook: Let's see, all together, I'll pay 8 bells for everything!" class="wp-image-7724" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;You can&amp;#8217;t give rotten acorns to Tortimer, so I filled up the recycle bin with them, and just sold the rest for 2 bells apiece.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I got to see the inside of Whitney&amp;#8217;s house now that she is all unpacked, and it looks nice!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/whitney-house-150x112.jpg" alt="The inside of Whitney's house in Animal Crossing: Wild World (ACWW)." class="wp-image-7725" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Octavian was still sick with a cold, so I gave him another dose of medicine.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;By the time I finished cleaning up all the acorns, I had given Tortimer 109 acorns in total. He gave me seven pieces of furniture in return: a mush lamp, stool, chair, stand, end table, dresser, and closet.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/cornimer-109-150x112.jpg" alt="Cornimer: The number of acorns you've given me is 109!" class="wp-image-7726" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I checked my storage to see if I had any leftover acorns there, but I didn&amp;#8217;t. So I sold my seven mush items at the store, and Tom Nook paid 15,600 bells for them all.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The Acorn Festival continues through Sunday, so you still have time to check it out for yourself! Good luck out there!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c27d879b16e3317f0d6fa350680e5023?s=98&amp;#038;d=mm&amp;#038;r=g' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt; &lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2024/10/10/acorn-festival-2024/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2024-10-10T19:02:09-04:00"&gt;October 10, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2024-10-10T19:04:37-04:00"&gt;October 10, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/acorn-fortune2024.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>October Arrives - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACCF Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2024/10/05/october-arrives/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2024/10/05/october-arrives/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 06 Oct 2024 03:55:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-13033" class="post-13033 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;October Arrives&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;October has arrived, and you can now purchase candy for Halloween at Tom Nook&amp;#8217;s shop. As a reminder, I do have a &lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/guides/accf/halloween.shtml"&gt;Halloween guide&lt;/a&gt; if you&amp;#8217;d like to refresh your memory on how it all works before the event comes at the end of the month.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The new month also brings a pukey, yellowish shade of grass. Fortunately, I played at night, when it doesn&amp;#8217;t look quite as bad. Just don&amp;#8217;t look directly at the pukey grass in direct sunlight! 😆 This is the ugliest time of year for grass, in my opinion.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jeremiah told me that Midge was making fun of his catchphrase, nee-deep. So he asked me to come up with a new phrase for him, and I told him to say &amp;#8220;I ate it.&amp;#8221; Hopefully it will pay off at some point in the coming weeks.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/RUU_8035-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Jeremiah: You said I ate it, right?" class="wp-image-13037" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Big Top was sick with a cold tonight, so I gave him some medicine that I bought at Nook &amp;#8216;n&amp;#8217; Go. He slurped it down as he did a backflip; not an easy task for an elephant!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/RUU_8031-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Big Top backflips as he takes his medicine." class="wp-image-13034" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;At the Roost, K.K. performed &amp;#8220;K.K. Marathon&amp;#8221; for me. It&amp;#8217;s one of my least-favorite songs in the game, at least when performed live. I&amp;#8217;d rather listen to K.K. recite bad poetry in Bebebese than suffer through this dreadfully boring tune.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/RUU_8032-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="K.K.: All right, get ready to dig the riffs on this ditty: K.K. Marathon." class="wp-image-13035" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Mint was talking about catching bugs, and she said it makes her want to &lt;em&gt;do it&lt;/em&gt;. Wait, what? 🤔&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/RUU_8033-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Mint: When I think about catching bugs, it really makes me want to go do it, ahhhhhh." class="wp-image-13036" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;I guess she&amp;#8217;s looking to catch some flies.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;In the city, I stopped in Crazy Redd&amp;#8217;s shop before he closed up for the night. He had these three items for sale:&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/RUU_8034-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Crazy Redd's items for sale tonight." class="wp-image-13038" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;A wistful painting that&amp;#8217;s lovely to see.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;A rocket to launch you to a new galaxy.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;A phone box for gossip, for you and your tea.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;    &lt;p&gt;That&amp;#8217;s all for now, but I&amp;#8217;ll see you next time! Never Stop Crossing!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2024/10/05/october-arrives/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2024-10-05T23:55:00-04:00"&gt;October 5, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2024-10-06T01:49:32-04:00"&gt;October 6, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/RUU_8035-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Purification Fee - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/10/05/purification-fee/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/10/05/purification-fee/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 06 Oct 2024 00:14:02 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8365" class="post-8365 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Purification Fee&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Monday, Rio told me that she recently had an argument with Agent S. So she asked me to deliver a gift to smooth things over. I hopped over to the squirrel&amp;#8217;s house and handed over the present. It was a metal can, which seemed a bit minimalist (to put it nicely).&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/agents-can-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Agent S: A metal can! Are you even SEEING this color? It's amaze-tastic!" class="wp-image-8367" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Her response seemed a little too enthusiastic for just a can, so I wondered if she was being sarcastic. Her next bit of dialogue also seemed to indicate that she knows the gift was junk. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/agents-garbage-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Agent S: Rio is the best! She knows me so well, it's almost like she goes through my garbage." class="wp-image-8368" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Tuesday was October 1st, and we&amp;#8217;re now headed into Halloween season. Jack (the czar of Halloween) sent me a letter reminding me to prepare for the event. He also sent me his portrait.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Candy is now available at Nook&amp;#8217;s Cranny (along with spooky furniture), and the shop has also started decorating for the holiday.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/oct-nook-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Nook's Cranny, decorated for Halloween." class="wp-image-8369" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;On Thursday, Ed the horse was camping over at the campsite. This is the 2nd time he has camped here (the first time was in &lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2023/11/15/im-not-a-squirrel/"&gt;November 2023&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/ed-camper2-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Ed, camping at the campsite: Hey, you're a local, right? The name's Ed." class="wp-image-8370" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Tonight, I went over to the plaza for K.K. Slider&amp;#8217;s concert. June, Louie, Rio, and Agent S joined me for a performance of &amp;#8220;K.K. Reggae.&amp;#8221; After the show, Agent S told me the best thing about autumn:&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/agents-fall-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Agent S: Fall fashion, duh! It's the one time all year I can wear my It's Fall Y'all! sweatshirt and not get funny looks!" class="wp-image-8373" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;I would still give you funny looks for that. 😛&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Next, I flew out to Harv&amp;#8217;s island, where I paid Katrina 1,000 bells to tell my fortune.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/katrina-restroom-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Katrina: A tummy rumbles... A restroom calls... Perhaps you've eaten a little too much?" class="wp-image-8374" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She told me that my health will diminish!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/katrina-health-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Katrina: From this vision, I deduce that your luck with health...will diminish..." class="wp-image-8375" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She insisted that something unfortunate might happen today, but fortunately she knew how to purify me. 😛 For a fee, of course.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/katrina-10k-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Katrina: Let me see... Shall I purify you for... 10,000 bells?" class="wp-image-8376" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I agreed to it, because I thought she might give me a rare item or something. She told me to close my eyes, while she let out a scream.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/katrina-scream-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Katrina, looking into her glowing crystal ball: YEEeeeeee!" class="wp-image-8377" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&amp;#8230;and that was it. She said I&amp;#8217;d be fine now. I didn&amp;#8217;t even get a lucky hat out of it. 😛 Oh well.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/katrina-fine-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Katrina: Now you should be fine." class="wp-image-8378" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;After that bit of excitement, I wrapped up my game for the night. But here are a few other quick notes about this week:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;Last Sunday, K.K. performed Hypno K.K. for me, Ankha, Merengue, and Bob.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;I helped out Gullivarrr on Monday, and he sent me a sea captain&amp;#8217;s coat on Tuesday.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Yesterday, I shot down a balloon present that contained 30,000 bells. Those are pretty rare, but always a pleasant surprise! 💰&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Enjoy the rest of your weekend, and I&amp;#8217;ll see you next time!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/10/05/purification-fee/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2024-10-05T20:14:02-04:00"&gt;October 5, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2024-10-05T20:18:35-04:00"&gt;October 5, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/agents-can-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
